{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6c30f265-8e52-4bc7-9bc6-38ccef25c4d5","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter updating, run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nAlso check for any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) that need version bumps to their .NET 11-compatible releases.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1b727033-e602-49b0-83d1-0e6cfec95187","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to search their codebase since they described the files. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":282,"requestId":"B421:389019:8B408E:AD21A6:6A01358B"},"id":"f94c773d-b5f1-41b8-82c9-5a504813e16a","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:49:22.119Z","parentId":"fd3af94c-27d5-4da1-a7f3-21997e08804b"}
